lwanga (1.0.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added logical AND (&&) and OR (||) operators for proper boolean logic
  * Precise SourceLocation tracking for all AST expression nodes
  * Error messages now show exact line and column numbers for all type failures
  * Fixed argument type mismatch errors to pinpoint exact argument location
  * Fixed duplicate parameter reporting with precise location
  * Fixed function tutorial examples that were using unsupported syntax
  * All type checking errors now display error[E#] with line:column pointers

 -- Cosmc Technologies <cosmahke4@gmail.com>  Mon, 03 Mar 2026 10:00:00 +0000

lwanga (1.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Compiler hardening and stability improvements
  * Support for *Type pointer syntax (e.g., let p: *u64)
  * Enhanced preprocessor with macro substitution (#define VAL 100)
  * Fixed array indexing for stack arrays and opaque pointers
  * Improved parser robustness and error recovery
  * Manual instruction demotion for LLVM 18+ obfuscation compatibility
  * Fixed missing linker dependencies in Debian package

 -- Cosmc Technologies <cosmahke4@gmail.com>  Tue, 24 Feb 2026 22:30:00 +0000

lwanga (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release
  * Full compiler with LLVM backend
  * Support for x86_64 and ARM64 architectures
  * Inline assembly support (Intel and AT&T syntax)
  * Direct syscall interface
  * Position-independent code generation
  * Encrypted string literals
  * Code formatter (lwangafmt) with logo headers
  * Syntax highlighter (lwangacat) with multiple themes
  * Comprehensive test suite (20+ tests)
  * Example programs included
  * File type icons and MIME type registration

